This paper is primarily focused on optimizing the energy cost of deep neural networks for mobile sensing applications, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically addresses the problem of cost-accuracy trade-off, which is a common concern in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) applications. The proposed framework involves the use of a selection module, which is a type of decision-making algorithm, and the REINFORCE algorithm, which is a type of reinforcement learning algorithm, both of which are relevant to the field of neural networks and deep learning (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves extensive experimentation with image classification datasets, which is a common application of data science (cs.DS).
